content:
Add the Supervisor Panel to the Salesforce Console

To make support supervisors' work easier, add the supervisor panel to the Salesforce console in Salesforce Classic. Supervisors can access information about their agents without switching between workspaces.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS

Available in: Performance Editions and Developer Edition orgs
Available in: Unlimited Edition and Enterprise Edition with Service Cloud
USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED

To set up Chat and manage apps: Customize Application

IMPORTANT The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026.

In Setup, enter Apps in the Quick Find box, then select App Manager.
Click Edit next to the Salesforce console app that you want to add the supervisor panel to.
In the Navigation Items tab, add Chat Supervisor to the Selected Items list.
Click Save.
title: Adding Supervisor Panel to Salesforce Console
